modules.description: This module provides parsers and utilities for converting between textual representations and structured data models of firewall rules, focusing on components like IP prefixes, port ranges, protocol specifiers (TCP/UDP/ICMP), and action directives (accept/drop). It operates on character streams to produce typed values such as IP family identifiers, ICMP type codes, and rule metadata, with specialized handling for QubesOS-specific formats including DPI strings and destination port ranges. The parsers enable validating and transforming raw rule strings into manipulable rule structures while preserving semantic details like protocol constraints and address family requirements.

This module parses and transforms textual firewall rule specifications into structured data models, handling components like IP prefixes, port ranges, protocols, and actions. It processes character streams to produce typed values such as IP families, ICMP codes, and rule metadata, with support for QubesOS-specific formats like DPI strings and port ranges. Main data types include rule structures with protocol constraints and address family requirements, while operations focus on validation, parsing, and transformation. Examples include converting raw rule strings into typed representations and extracting structured port and protocol information from QubesOS-formatted inputs.
